WEBVTT

00:03.712 --> 00:06.840
My husband was
 considering you for his portrait

00:06.881 --> 00:10.343
but you took yourself
      out of contention. Why?

00:10.385 --> 00:12.012
I was only interested
         in painting you.

00:14.180 --> 00:16.683
I'm sure he'll be glad
           to hear that.

00:16.725 --> 00:18.184
Well, the thing is,
          the president,

00:18.226 --> 00:20.311
even a Black president,
        is the institution.

00:20.353 --> 00:22.480
I don't wanna just paint
           the official.

00:22.522 --> 00:24.691
I am interested in the real.

00:26.401 --> 00:28.028
...across America starting at--

00:29.696 --> 00:32.198
Washington can be
        an awfully tough town,

00:32.240 --> 00:34.075
on a political wife.
           Would you agree?

00:35.118 --> 00:37.370
Well, I agree.

00:37.412 --> 00:40.707
But I had, you see,
        26 years experience...

00:40.749 --> 00:42.792
as the wife of a congressman.

00:43.710 --> 00:46.880
But I think a congressional wife

00:46.921 --> 00:50.759
has to be a special kind
             of woman.

00:50.800 --> 00:53.762
I don't think all women really

00:53.803 --> 00:57.265
can adjust to this type
               of life.

01:11.112 --> 01:14.491
"The battle
   for individual rights of women

01:14.532 --> 01:16.409
is one of long standing,

01:16.451 --> 01:18.828
and none of us
          should countenance

01:18.870 --> 01:21.331
anything which undermines it."

01:22.207 --> 01:25.919
"People say,
        no woman could stand

01:25.960 --> 01:30.256
the physical strain
          a man endures.

01:30.298 --> 01:33.384
But that, I think is nonsense.

01:33.426 --> 01:37.097
A woman is like a tea bag,

01:37.138 --> 01:40.058
you never know how strong it is

01:40.100 --> 01:42.685
until it's in hot water."

01:47.524 --> 01:49.609
This land is your land

01:52.612 --> 01:54.906
This land is my land

01:57.909 --> 02:00.411
From California

02:01.663 --> 02:05.667
Well, to the New York Island

02:06.835 --> 02:10.296
From the Redwood Forest

02:11.923 --> 02:15.802
To the Gulf Stream Waters

02:16.970 --> 02:21.641
I tell you this land

02:21.683 --> 02:24.811
Was made for you and me

02:24.853 --> 02:26.020
Yeah

02:27.355 --> 02:30.567
Mmm

02:31.609 --> 02:36.281
One bright, sunny morning

02:36.322 --> 02:40.160
Well, in the shadow
            of a steeple

02:41.202 --> 02:45.456
Down by the welfare office

02:45.498 --> 02:49.627
I saw my people

02:50.628 --> 02:55.383
I was wondering if this land

02:55.425 --> 03:00.305
Was made for you and me

03:08.188 --> 03:11.024
Sasha, stop it.
   You can't have any more. No--

03:13.193 --> 03:15.445
Listen,
     this is how it's gonna go.

03:16.404 --> 03:18.489
When we get to Washington,

03:18.531 --> 03:21.159
Grandma's gonna meet us
           at the hotel,

03:21.201 --> 03:22.660
and then Daddy and I
          are gonna go see

03:22.702 --> 03:25.538
the Bushes at the White House.
               Okay?

03:26.414 --> 03:27.874
Look!

03:33.421 --> 03:34.714
It's Dad.

03:34.756 --> 03:36.299
-Uh-huh.

03:37.258 --> 03:39.010
Let's go see Daddy.

03:45.600 --> 03:48.186
-Mrs. Obama!

03:48.228 --> 03:50.396
-Mrs. Obama!

03:54.150 --> 03:56.569
-Mrs. President!

04:00.240 --> 04:02.992
-Thank you.

04:03.034 --> 04:04.744
There they are.
         Come on, come on.

04:05.453 --> 04:08.706
Oh! 

04:08.748 --> 04:11.626
Look at you! You look so pretty.

04:11.668 --> 04:14.796
-The fuck?
   -Yeah, it's a lot. It's a lot.

04:15.964 --> 04:17.590
All right. You ready?

04:17.632 --> 04:20.843
We're gonna go on a little ride.
          You good? Okay.

