15:37.227 --> 15:39.188
Franklin, you're fresh
         on everyone's mind

15:39.229 --> 15:41.023
and the two of you, together,

15:41.065 --> 15:43.150
present a truly
         irresistible team.

15:46.987 --> 15:48.656
Yes, we do make a good team.

15:49.907 --> 15:50.908
Hmm.

15:52.326 --> 15:53.869
Thank you.

15:53.911 --> 15:56.080
-Croquet?
 -No, I'd rather be a spectator.

15:56.121 --> 15:57.915
-Cheers.
              -Cheers.

15:57.957 --> 15:59.792
Right, Eleanor, you're up!

15:59.833 --> 16:01.835
My turn. I believe I'm winning.

16:01.877 --> 16:05.130
-Well, you keep missing.
     -Watch out, Louis. Ha-ha!

16:15.474 --> 16:16.642
Help!

16:18.852 --> 16:20.145
Franklin?

16:24.817 --> 16:27.945
-Oh! What happened?
    -My legs. They won't work.

16:28.862 --> 16:30.739
I don't know what's going on.
              Please!

16:30.781 --> 16:32.157
I'll lift you up onto the bed.

16:32.199 --> 16:35.285
Ow! No, no, no, no! Ow! Ow! Ow!

16:35.327 --> 16:37.413
Oh, God. What's going on?

16:37.454 --> 16:38.998
Call Dr. Keen.

16:39.039 --> 16:43.919
-Oh. Ooh. Oh, you're burning up.

16:43.961 --> 16:46.797
-Franklin.
           -Ow!

16:46.839 --> 16:51.802
Oh, Franklin.
 It's all right. It's all right.

16:51.844 --> 16:55.389
Oh. For God's sake, stop.

16:55.431 --> 16:57.725
Oh, but Dr. Keen
 said this would help, Franklin.

16:57.766 --> 17:00.352
Well, it's not. It's making
      it worse. Please, stop!

17:00.394 --> 17:03.689
Let's stop. Stop.
        I'll call Dr. Keen.

17:04.857 --> 17:06.316
I want a second opinion.

17:07.109 --> 17:11.238
This isn't all right, Louis.
   It shouldn't be this painful.

17:14.366 --> 17:17.202
-I'm sorry, Franklin.
            -I'm sorry.

17:40.934 --> 17:42.102
Louis?

17:44.730 --> 17:45.898
Louis!

17:50.277 --> 17:51.612
Eleanor. What is it?

17:51.653 --> 17:53.697
-It's polio.
               -What?

17:53.739 --> 17:56.241
-It's polio.
         -What?

17:56.283 --> 17:59.536
Eleanor. Franklin is resting.

17:59.578 --> 18:00.662
Sara.

18:01.330 --> 18:04.708
All of the specialists
     confirmed that it's polio.

18:06.043 --> 18:07.669
Well, that's not possible.

18:08.587 --> 18:10.547
They say that it is.

18:10.589 --> 18:14.051
-But he's not a child.
    -That it can affect adults.

18:14.093 --> 18:17.930
Well-- How? Well, what are you
       looking at here? Um...

18:17.971 --> 18:21.225
It was the standing water
           in the cove.

18:21.266 --> 18:24.311
The virus was
 just sitting there, apparently.

18:24.353 --> 18:28.065
He must've contracted it
      when they swam that day.

18:28.107 --> 18:29.399
What? No.

18:29.441 --> 18:31.985
My son can't have polio.

18:32.027 --> 18:34.071
No, no, I don't believe it.

18:34.696 --> 18:36.115
I don't believe it. No.

18:46.458 --> 18:48.502
Oh. Oh, my God.

18:51.630 --> 18:53.590
Oh, my God.

18:56.260 --> 18:57.636
Eleanor.

19:02.516 --> 19:04.143
Eleanor...

19:06.728 --> 19:08.981
No one can find out.

19:09.022 --> 19:12.943
They must protect him.
         Give him purpose.

19:12.985 --> 19:15.612
If anyone can rise
   above tragedy, it's Franklin.

19:16.780 --> 19:19.491
Well, I'm sure glad you're here,
               Louis.

19:46.476 --> 19:48.061
Nell, dear...

19:51.064 --> 19:55.194
I wanted to tell you. I'm sorry
 your mother was taken so soon.

19:57.154 --> 19:59.531
You and your brother,
   you're going to be all right.

20:00.574 --> 20:01.867
I promise you that.

20:03.076 --> 20:05.037
You're a good girl, Eleanor.

20:06.413 --> 20:07.915
Thanks, Uncle Teddy.

20:14.087 --> 20:16.882
Daddy, can we go home now?

20:16.924 --> 20:20.219
Grandma Mary will
   take you and your baby brother

20:20.260 --> 20:22.012
to her house for a while.

20:22.930 --> 20:24.723
I need to go away for a rest.

20:25.599 --> 20:27.893
But then we'll go with you.

20:27.935 --> 20:30.812
It's not that kind
          of a rest, now.

20:32.481 --> 20:34.900
Your Uncle Teddy has a plan
       to get me well again.

20:34.942 --> 20:37.110
And as soon as I get better,
        I will come see you.

20:37.152 --> 20:38.403
No, but I can help you.

20:38.445 --> 20:42.366
I know you can. 

20:42.407 --> 20:43.784
And I need your help.

20:43.825 --> 20:46.119
I need you to go
       with your grandmother

20:46.161 --> 20:48.247
and take care
       of your baby brother,

20:48.288 --> 20:50.040
just the way your mother would.

20:50.082 --> 20:51.500
Can you do that for me,

20:51.541 --> 20:53.418
just till I come back
           good as new?

21:23.991 --> 21:26.743
Good evening.
   Under heavy pressure to resign,

21:26.785 --> 21:29.454
some of it coming from
   strong supporters of the past.

21:29.496 --> 21:31.957
President Nixon headed
        for Washington without,

21:31.999 --> 21:33.583
according to a spokesman,

21:33.625 --> 21:35.460
talking to his two
          Watergate lawyers,

21:35.502 --> 21:37.004
whom he had summoned
             to Florida.

21:37.045 --> 21:38.755
Meantime,
        the man Mr. Nixon chose

21:38.797 --> 21:40.799
to be vice president,
             Gerald Ford,

21:40.841 --> 21:43.635
faced his own pressure before
      the Senate Rules Committee.

21:43.677 --> 21:45.137
Transparency and honesty

21:45.178 --> 21:46.972
are at a premium right now.

21:47.014 --> 21:49.308
Facing questions over his use
          of a psychiatrist,

21:49.349 --> 21:51.476
Congressman Ford failed
          to deliver either.

21:51.518 --> 21:53.270
Congressman Ford, do you deny

21:53.312 --> 21:55.272
meeting with this psychiatrist?

21:55.314 --> 21:59.985
Maybe I've met with him
     once or twice, uh, socially.

22:00.027 --> 22:03.322
Ran into him at the, uh--
             The club or--

22:03.363 --> 22:05.115
He is
     in your appointments calendar

22:05.157 --> 22:07.576
at least, uh, twice
           that we can find.

22:09.202 --> 22:11.747
His silence spoke volumes.

22:11.788 --> 22:15.167
-   In other Watergate news...
      -Oh, fuck a duck, Jerry.

22:15.208 --> 22:17.252
Well, he's screwed now.

22:17.294 --> 22:19.338
...first jail sentence against
           Donald Segretti,

22:19.379 --> 22:22.299
the man known as
        "dirty-trick" Donald...

22:22.341 --> 22:23.383
Sorry.

22:26.219 --> 22:28.013
-Betty, congratulations.
        -Thank you so much.

22:28.055 --> 22:30.098
I'm so happy for you.
       They're ready for you.

22:31.725 --> 22:36.021
Today, the Congressional Club
   has a very special opportunity

22:36.063 --> 22:38.065
to honor one of our own.

22:38.106 --> 22:40.692
On the eve of her being
         officially named

22:40.734 --> 22:44.363
our new Second Lady, Betty Ford.

22:50.786 --> 22:51.870
Thank you, Jill.

23:04.883 --> 23:06.468
Thank you, Jill.

23:06.510 --> 23:08.929
--And thank you, ladies.

23:13.016 --> 23:15.894
It's wonderful
        to be up here after

23:15.936 --> 23:19.689
over a decade
     as a member of this group.

23:25.028 --> 23:26.863
I know what
       you're all thinking...

23:30.075 --> 23:32.536
The way her husband's hearing
            went today,

23:32.577 --> 23:36.039
is she even going to be
           Second Lady?

23:36.081 --> 23:38.959
-Yes.

23:45.006 --> 23:47.801
Well, let me tell you
         about something.

23:50.011 --> 23:52.264
Uh, nearly ten years ago,

23:52.305 --> 23:55.225
I pinched a nerve in my neck.

23:55.267 --> 23:57.936
During the course
          of treatment...

23:59.646 --> 24:03.191
my doctor, uh, advised me

24:03.233 --> 24:05.777
that the source of my pain...

24:08.405 --> 24:12.159
It was actually much deeper

24:12.200 --> 24:15.120
than any injury.

24:16.455 --> 24:19.207
And he thought

24:20.167 --> 24:23.503
it might be
    a good idea for me to see...

24:25.589 --> 24:26.631
a psychiatrist.

24:33.013 --> 24:37.142
And it was a good idea.

24:46.526 --> 24:50.572
For the first time,
     I was able to verbalize...

24:55.452 --> 24:57.120
We love our husbands, right?

24:59.080 --> 25:02.250
-Yes.
       -Right? Okay.

25:02.292 --> 25:07.214
But every night
        he's at a fundraiser

25:07.255 --> 25:12.302
or a speech
       in some faraway city.

25:12.344 --> 25:15.847
Then he comes home
    right at the kids' bedtime,

25:15.889 --> 25:19.142
disrupts the entire household,

25:19.184 --> 25:21.269
then he heads into the bedroom,

25:21.311 --> 25:25.941
and you go downstairs
      to heat up some dinner,

25:25.982 --> 25:29.945
and mix cocktails,
    but when you come back up...

25:31.071 --> 25:32.197
he's snoring.

25:36.243 --> 25:39.204
And you're left holding
          two cocktails.

25:41.540 --> 25:44.626
But this is what we signed up
           for ladies...

25:45.752 --> 25:48.713
when we married politicians.

25:51.800 --> 25:56.304
But that psychiatrist
          reminded me...

25:57.931 --> 26:02.102
that my life isn't only about
            those days.

26:05.063 --> 26:09.025
There is a Betty
        without Jerry Ford.

26:11.653 --> 26:14.990
And that Betty needs to
             make sure

26:15.031 --> 26:17.117
that she's healthy,

26:17.158 --> 26:20.245
before she can do anything else.

26:24.082 --> 26:27.752
It was my psychiatrist
       Jerry met with twice.

26:27.794 --> 26:29.671
My psychiatrist...

26:30.463 --> 26:32.090
you heard discussed

26:32.132 --> 26:35.802
in his confirmation hearings
           this morning.

26:36.803 --> 26:40.932
He met with my psychiatrist,
           to support me.

26:40.974 --> 26:43.935
And I love him for that.

26:50.817 --> 26:55.447
And for letting me be the one
        to explain that...

26:55.488 --> 26:58.158
-Yes! Absolutely. Well done!
    -...to the American people.

26:58.199 --> 26:59.701
Well done!

27:00.285 --> 27:01.453
Yes.

27:15.091 --> 27:16.259
That's great, Franklin.

27:16.301 --> 27:17.802
Wave to the crowd.

27:20.513 --> 27:21.556
Whoo!

27:28.063 --> 27:30.732
--Father, are you okay?

27:30.774 --> 27:35.487
Oh. Oh. Better than okay.
 He made it nine steps this time.

27:37.197 --> 27:38.990
-I'll get there.
     -Oh, of course, you will.

27:39.032 --> 27:41.326
-Can't we just move the podium?

27:41.368 --> 27:43.995
I can't control the proportions
        of the room, James.

27:44.037 --> 27:45.205
I wish I could.

27:48.708 --> 27:50.752
We'll try it again.

27:50.794 --> 27:53.338
Don't you think he needs a break
   Mother? Jesus, he's bleeding.

27:56.216 --> 27:59.010
And so I am. James, I am fine.

27:59.052 --> 28:03.139
All I need is a glass of water
     and we will do this again.

28:03.181 --> 28:06.059
-I'll get it.
        -That's the spirit.

28:06.101 --> 28:07.769
--Right, let's take a break.

28:07.811 --> 28:09.270
Louis. Louis, hold on.

28:09.312 --> 28:11.398
Just give me a moment, boys.

28:11.439 --> 28:13.525
-Please, just a moment.
        -Yes, yes.

28:17.320 --> 28:21.408
I hope you never have to see
       your son in such pain.

28:23.868 --> 28:26.329
Sara, you know
      that he's wanted to run

28:26.371 --> 28:28.164
for governor for a decade now.

28:28.206 --> 28:30.250
Maybe longer.

28:30.291 --> 28:33.962
And with these braces,
    he's finally got his chance.

28:34.003 --> 28:37.424
As I told you before
           many years ago

28:37.465 --> 28:40.468
when this nightmare began,

28:40.510 --> 28:43.138
he should be retired and living

28:43.179 --> 28:46.015
at Hyde Park
       in a dignified manner.

28:46.057 --> 28:49.394
Not falling and-- And bleeding,

28:49.436 --> 28:53.690
and being humiliated
      for an impossible idea.

28:53.732 --> 28:58.653
Unprecedented. Not impossible.

28:58.695 --> 29:00.155
Oh...

29:00.196 --> 29:03.533
People admire resilience.

29:03.575 --> 29:05.869
They are inspired by it.

29:05.910 --> 29:09.205
It shows them that they too
           can overcome

29:09.247 --> 29:13.168
the most unspeakable setbacks.

29:14.377 --> 29:16.212
And you know,

29:16.254 --> 29:18.673
Governor was always
         on the next step

29:18.715 --> 29:20.383
of the ladder
        to the White House.

29:20.425 --> 29:22.135
The White House!

29:22.177 --> 29:26.639
You're so cruel when you
    encourage these pipe dreams.

29:27.724 --> 29:30.602
Franklin had a-a bright future.

29:30.643 --> 29:32.437
Impossibly bright.

29:32.479 --> 29:35.690
There was nothing my son
    couldn't have accomplished.

29:35.732 --> 29:40.612
But that was before.
     It is no longer, Eleanor.

29:40.653 --> 29:45.700
I'm sorry, Sara,
    but I respectfully disagree.

29:45.742 --> 29:49.913
I think there is nothing
      that Franklin can't do.

29:50.914 --> 29:53.958
So, you'll keep at it then?

29:54.000 --> 29:56.461
It's what he wants, Sara.

29:56.503 --> 30:01.257
I think you better think up
           a backup plan

30:01.299 --> 30:03.134
for when he loses.

30:06.596 --> 30:09.641
He's not going to lose.

30:09.682 --> 30:12.393
So Mrs. R
       with all her trimmin's

30:12.435 --> 30:14.395
Can broadcast a bed
            from Simmons

30:14.437 --> 30:17.232
'Cause Franklin knows

30:17.273 --> 30:20.193
Anything goes

30:38.336 --> 30:40.672
Mrs. Alberta King
          sat at the organ

30:40.713 --> 30:42.549
in the Ebenezer Baptist Church

30:42.590 --> 30:45.218
when a young man sprang
      to his feet and yelled,

30:45.260 --> 30:47.846
"I'm going to kill everyone
             in here."

30:47.887 --> 30:50.306
And shot Mrs. King three times.

30:50.348 --> 30:52.475
Well, it's as if the King family
          is being tested.

30:52.517 --> 30:55.478
I've never seen a family suffer
    so much tragedy in my life.

31:09.909 --> 31:12.203
-Mr. Cheney.
          -He's available?

31:12.245 --> 31:13.371
Of course.

31:19.419 --> 31:21.421
-Mr. Rumsfeld, sir.
               -Yes?

31:23.256 --> 31:25.383
Are you aware
     the vice president's wife

31:25.425 --> 31:27.927
has requested the jet
    for Alberta King's funeral?

31:29.470 --> 31:31.055
-Has she?
              -Yeah.

31:33.308 --> 31:35.310
Well, thank you, Dick.

31:35.894 --> 31:37.061
Thank you, sir.

31:57.790 --> 31:59.375
Mr. Rumsfeld.

32:00.543 --> 32:02.420
Are you joining us today?

32:03.630 --> 32:06.215
I had to warn you
        when I heard, ma'am.

32:06.257 --> 32:09.260
It is not appropriate for you
 to represent the administration

32:09.302 --> 32:10.720
at Mrs. King's funeral.

32:10.762 --> 32:12.013
I wasn't aware
         the administration

32:12.055 --> 32:16.351
found compassion inappropriate.

32:16.392 --> 32:18.603
Well, we both know
        that's not accurate.

32:18.645 --> 32:23.107
I guess that explains why
   I'll be the only person there

32:23.149 --> 32:25.026
representing the White House.

32:26.486 --> 32:28.071
It was a tragic event.

32:28.112 --> 32:30.907
No, the tragedy is that
     this kind of thing happens

32:30.949 --> 32:34.160
every day in this country

32:34.202 --> 32:36.329
and no one bats an eye.

32:36.371 --> 32:40.416
Have you given any thought
         to what's coming?

32:42.627 --> 32:46.756
We both know Nixon won't survive
        this Watergate mess.

32:46.798 --> 32:48.967
You'll be walking into ten times

32:49.008 --> 32:50.802
the scrutiny
      that you've ever faced.

32:50.843 --> 32:53.304
Scrutiny of every skeleton.
           Every closet.

32:54.722 --> 32:56.516
Scrutiny of your first husband.

33:04.607 --> 33:05.692
Susie.

33:06.693 --> 33:08.069
It's Susan.

33:09.696 --> 33:13.116
Jerry's already asked me
     to be his chief of staff.

33:13.157 --> 33:16.035
So that means I'll be everywhere
          all of the time.

33:17.036 --> 33:20.123
And, uh, if anyone...

33:20.164 --> 33:22.625
And I mean anyone,

33:22.667 --> 33:24.919
says things to the press
     or the congressional club,

33:24.961 --> 33:26.504
or to whomever
       that might jeopardize

33:26.546 --> 33:28.756
him staying in the White House,

33:28.798 --> 33:30.842
I have to stop them.

33:30.883 --> 33:35.847
My goodness, Don.
       What happened to you?

33:39.225 --> 33:42.687
I take my position
          very seriously.

33:48.192 --> 33:50.028
Let's get this plane in the air.

33:55.992 --> 33:59.370
Senseless violence
     took not only my wife...

34:01.497 --> 34:05.835
but my son,
       Martin Luther King Jr.

34:09.505 --> 34:11.507
My heart is wounded.

34:13.593 --> 34:17.138
My heart is bruised.

34:26.939 --> 34:28.733
But it is not broken!

34:28.775 --> 34:30.651
-Yes, Lord. Yes, Lord.
            -No!

34:30.693 --> 34:35.281
Amazing Grace

34:37.241 --> 34:42.288
--   How sweet the sound

34:45.291 --> 34:50.421
That saved a wretch

34:53.424 --> 34:58.471
like me

35:01.349 --> 35:05.436
I once

35:05.478 --> 35:09.315
was lost

35:09.357 --> 35:13.361
But now

35:13.402 --> 35:17.406
am found

35:17.448 --> 35:21.369
Was blind

35:21.410 --> 35:25.456
but now

35:25.498 --> 35:30.628
I see

35:33.923 --> 35:38.803
Through many

35:38.845 --> 35:41.472
dangers...

35:41.514 --> 35:44.392
With the South Side
      Healthcare Collaborative

35:44.433 --> 35:47.895
any patient who shows up
       in our emergency room

35:47.937 --> 35:50.064
who can't afford
       a primary care doctor

35:50.106 --> 35:52.150
will instantly
        be connected to one.

35:52.191 --> 35:54.068
Mmm.

35:54.110 --> 35:57.113
I'm talking about people who
     live outside these walls.

35:57.155 --> 36:01.951
Who sweep our floors, drive our
 city's buses, collect our trash.

36:01.993 --> 36:04.078
These are our neighbors.

36:04.120 --> 36:05.872
And if we believe
         that health care

36:05.913 --> 36:07.623
is not just for
        the privileged few,

36:08.541 --> 36:10.376
then it's time
        we served them too.

36:11.085 --> 36:12.545
All right, thank you.

36:12.587 --> 36:15.298
-Thanks, everyone.
       -Mm-hmm.

36:15.339 --> 36:18.050
I think making
    you VP of Community Affairs

36:18.092 --> 36:19.635
might be the best decision
            I ever made.

36:19.677 --> 36:21.512
Oh, I'm sorry. Your decision?

36:22.680 --> 36:24.265
Okay, fine. That was all Susan.

36:24.307 --> 36:26.434
-But, what I'm trying to say is,

36:26.475 --> 36:28.936
I hired an amazing person
    who hired an amazing person.

36:28.978 --> 36:30.855
So, I think I deserve
         a little credit.

36:32.899 --> 36:34.275
Thanks, Michelle.

36:36.319 --> 36:39.488
I gotta say, you are on a hell
     of a roll here, Michelle.

36:39.530 --> 36:41.365
-Mm-hmm.
      -And... 

36:41.407 --> 36:45.119
the noticeable increase in R & B
    soul music playing in the ER

36:45.161 --> 36:46.871
is my favorite part.

36:46.913 --> 36:49.540
We gotta sound like we're on
        the South Side too.

36:49.582 --> 36:51.209
-Mmm.

36:51.250 --> 36:53.002
And word on the street is,

36:53.044 --> 36:56.088
your life away from work might
    start getting a little busy.

36:56.130 --> 36:59.842
You mean Barack's campaign?
    That's his thing, not mine.

36:59.884 --> 37:03.512
His thing is running for
 president of the United States.

37:03.554 --> 37:07.141
Which, I imagine, could
     eventually mean everybody

37:07.183 --> 37:09.143
in his life kind of thing.

37:09.185 --> 37:12.521
Yeah, but we still don't know
   how far the campaign will go.

37:12.563 --> 37:14.774
And Barack knows
 I've got my own thing going on--

37:14.815 --> 37:16.275
Yeah, and I love that
          about you guys.

37:16.317 --> 37:18.778
I'm just saying
        it's a possibility.

37:18.819 --> 37:20.947
I have Sasha on the phone,

37:20.988 --> 37:22.949
calling mummy
        for the first time.

37:22.990 --> 37:25.034
Oh! We'll pick up on this later.

37:26.160 --> 37:28.037
Hi, bug. How you doing?

37:29.121 --> 37:30.748
Who?

37:30.790 --> 37:32.291
What do you mean,
      there are secret people

37:32.333 --> 37:33.584
all over the house?

37:44.971 --> 37:47.431
--Renaissance has landed.

37:47.473 --> 37:48.849
Ma'am.

37:48.891 --> 37:51.394
Hey, brother.
       Who the hell are you?

37:51.435 --> 37:53.062
Agent Allen Taylor, ma'am.

37:53.104 --> 37:54.981
Sorry for the inconvenience.

37:55.022 --> 37:57.692
Your protective detail
           starts today.

37:58.526 --> 38:00.152
Shit!

38:00.194 --> 38:01.946
Protection unit on scene.

38:04.573 --> 38:07.994
-...   received.
 -Hey, honey. You're home early.

38:08.035 --> 38:09.829
Protective detail?

38:09.870 --> 38:11.580
-You're not even a nominee yet.
      -I know, right. It's--

38:11.622 --> 38:12.999
Where are the girls?

38:16.043 --> 38:17.920
-You're okay?
     -Good morning!

38:17.962 --> 38:19.630
Hmm? Mm-hmm.

38:19.672 --> 38:21.507
-Mommy's here.
     -We're fine.

38:21.549 --> 38:23.384
Hi.

38:23.426 --> 38:24.468
That's why
    the secret people are here.

38:24.510 --> 38:26.304
To protect us.

38:26.345 --> 38:28.014
Well, that's what Dad said.

38:29.098 --> 38:31.309
-One of them gave me candy.
           -Spit it out.

38:31.350 --> 38:33.227
-But, Mom.
     -No candy from strangers,

38:33.269 --> 38:34.186
you know that.

38:35.396 --> 38:36.439
Give it to me.

38:36.480 --> 38:37.815
Mm-mmm.

38:39.483 --> 38:40.526
I told you.

38:44.447 --> 38:45.489
Come here.

38:47.033 --> 38:48.200
-Be good.
             -Mm-hmm.

39:01.380 --> 39:05.593
Boom. Your man kicked the
 Secret Service out of the house.

39:05.634 --> 39:07.887
I said, "Look, fellas..."

39:07.928 --> 39:09.597
"...I don't care how many guns
              you got.

39:09.638 --> 39:11.724
My wife doesn't like it.
         Get to steppin'."

39:11.766 --> 39:14.685
Now, strictly speaking,
   they can't leave the property,

39:15.227 --> 39:16.562
but-- 

39:16.604 --> 39:18.689
-Come on.
      -It's not funny, Barack.

39:19.732 --> 39:22.693
There are men with guns
         outside our home.

39:24.195 --> 39:26.113
Did they say why now?

39:26.155 --> 39:28.866
Well, look, there-there--
   There have been some threats.

39:28.908 --> 39:32.536
-Some letters, message boards.
     -There are death threats?

39:38.167 --> 39:41.587
Well, hey, look, baby,
       we always knew there--

39:41.629 --> 39:42.922
There would be some crazies.

39:42.963 --> 39:45.508
Yeah. When did you plan
          on telling me?

39:47.009 --> 39:50.054
Uh. Well, uh, I-I was gonna,

39:50.096 --> 39:51.847
but I-I didn't want you
           to freak out.

39:51.889 --> 39:53.891
Well, you certainly failed
              at that.

39:55.059 --> 39:57.853
Well, look--

39:57.895 --> 40:00.815
I mean, Mich, th-this kind
 of thing happens at this level.

40:00.856 --> 40:02.149
Really?

40:02.191 --> 40:04.318
John Edwards
        have Secret Service?

40:04.360 --> 40:06.654
What about John McCain?
           Mitt Romney?

40:06.695 --> 40:10.408
-Probably not.
        -Yeah. You know why?

40:11.575 --> 40:13.077
-You're a coon.

40:13.119 --> 40:15.204
You're a nigga,

40:15.246 --> 40:18.249
running for president
       of the United States.

40:18.290 --> 40:21.252
So, yeah, there's a little
 difference between you and those

40:21.293 --> 40:23.170
-other candidates, Barack.
              -Just--

40:24.964 --> 40:28.759
Um, I could be president
       of the United States.

40:28.801 --> 40:31.762
Can you find it in yourself
   to be a little excited for me?

40:31.804 --> 40:33.931
Excuse me if I can't share
         in the excitement

40:33.973 --> 40:36.267
of my husband potentially
            being shot.

40:36.308 --> 40:38.978
It is interesting to me
      that you're more willing

40:39.019 --> 40:40.563
to believe in me being--

40:40.604 --> 40:42.940
It be me being shot,
      than me being president.

40:42.982 --> 40:44.942
Oh, no. I think it's interesting

40:44.984 --> 40:47.611
that you're willing to put your
 family in harm's way because of

40:47.653 --> 40:49.613
-your insatiable ambition.
    -Don't do it. Don't do that.

40:49.655 --> 40:50.698
Don't do that.

40:52.491 --> 40:54.160
-You know what?

40:54.827 --> 40:56.579
Remember Jackie Kennedy?

40:58.122 --> 41:00.291
Her blood-splattered,
         pink Chanel suit?

41:01.292 --> 41:02.960
Her kids had to see that.

41:03.002 --> 41:05.713
Someone had to explain that
         to them, Barack.

41:05.754 --> 41:07.590
-Jackie Kennedy?
               -Yeah.

41:07.631 --> 41:11.093
Martin, Malcolm, all of the
   above, this is not about that.

41:11.135 --> 41:14.555
This is about the fact that
   you don't want me in politics.

41:14.597 --> 41:17.641
You have never wanted me
            in politics.

41:17.683 --> 41:20.728
So, just own up to that,
       hold that, all right?

41:20.769 --> 41:24.607
Because we've been through the
   security details meticulously

41:24.648 --> 41:26.484
at your request, right?

41:26.525 --> 41:29.153
You came in here
       with open eyes, so...

41:35.075 --> 41:36.160
Mich?

41:37.536 --> 41:39.038
Mich?

41:39.079 --> 41:41.332
Make sure the girls brush
        their teeth later.

42:06.732 --> 42:09.527
Just needed some
         daddy-chair time.

42:09.568 --> 42:11.278
He used to love that old thing.

42:12.488 --> 42:14.198
Still smells of him.

42:14.240 --> 42:15.366
Yeah.

42:17.201 --> 42:18.244
Yeah.

42:20.829 --> 42:22.456
-Mama.

42:32.550 --> 42:35.386
Oh, my God! Oh, my God!
      Oh, my God! Oh, my God!

42:35.427 --> 42:37.555
-Are you okay, baby?
       -What's got into you?

42:37.596 --> 42:40.558
-I got into Princeton! 
   -Oh, honey! That's wonderful!

42:40.599 --> 42:42.226
-That's amazing.
     -They would've been fools

42:42.268 --> 42:43.852
not to accept you.

42:43.894 --> 42:45.354
I'm gonna scare all the boys
           away from you.

42:45.396 --> 42:47.898
-Oh, you would do that! 

42:47.940 --> 42:49.984
Oh, what is it, Mommy?

42:54.363 --> 42:56.115
Oh.

42:56.156 --> 42:58.576
They're not offering
         any financial aid?

43:00.536 --> 43:03.205
I'm sorry.
    I got so excited when I saw,

43:03.247 --> 43:04.915
"Congratulations,
         you're admitted."

43:04.957 --> 43:06.417
-I stopped reading right there.
         -Don't be sorry.

43:06.458 --> 43:08.419
This is a big deal.
        You should be happy.

43:08.460 --> 43:10.588
But how are we gonna pay for it?

43:10.629 --> 43:14.508
You did the work to get in.
   You leave this part up to us.

43:14.550 --> 43:16.510
We got room to take on
           another loan.

43:16.552 --> 43:18.846
-You guys--
      -Uh-uh-uh. Listen to me.

43:18.887 --> 43:20.014
You belong there.

43:20.055 --> 43:21.432
Just do your thing.

43:24.893 --> 43:26.270
-Thank you.
           -Mmm.

43:31.775 --> 43:34.778
So, what's going on?

43:39.158 --> 43:40.409
It's nothing.

43:43.537 --> 43:46.081
Does "nothing" mean you married
             a tornado

43:46.123 --> 43:50.961
that turned everything you ever
     planned for in your life,

43:51.003 --> 43:52.588
upside down?

43:55.966 --> 43:59.595
I'm just terrified my girls
           are gonna see

43:59.637 --> 44:03.641
their daddy's picture hanging
    on someone's wall, like a--

44:03.682 --> 44:06.101
Another dead Black hero.

44:06.143 --> 44:07.519
Baby...

44:08.771 --> 44:12.191
it seems you got two choices.

44:13.525 --> 44:17.404
Both of them ending with that
   man doing what he's gonna do.

44:19.698 --> 44:21.825
Well, what-- What should I do?

44:27.039 --> 44:31.168
You know what your daddy
       used to say about you.

44:37.216 --> 44:40.010
Mich? Shit.

44:41.637 --> 44:43.681
You can't tell
         that girl nothin'!

44:56.318 --> 44:57.361
Mmm.

44:58.278 --> 44:59.363
Yeah.

45:12.334 --> 45:14.545
Still, with the
       election 18 months away,

45:14.586 --> 45:16.088
it is notable that Obama is

45:16.130 --> 45:18.006
the earliest candidate
           to ever receive

45:18.048 --> 45:20.384
-   a government security detail.

45:23.262 --> 45:24.304
Hey.

45:25.723 --> 45:26.765
Mmm.

45:29.268 --> 45:30.352
You're still at it?

45:32.896 --> 45:35.482
Ninety percent of running
           for president

45:35.524 --> 45:36.900
-is reading memos

45:36.942 --> 45:38.402
and the other ten is wondering

45:38.444 --> 45:40.904
why the fuck you ran
        in the first place.

45:45.534 --> 45:47.244
So, how are we?

45:54.293 --> 45:55.377
I--

45:57.129 --> 46:00.048
I-I met this little, old lady,
 she grabbed a hold of me, says,

46:00.090 --> 46:03.093
"Mr. Obama,
 I sure hope you become president

46:03.844 --> 46:07.973
because I'm sick and tired
    of lying to my grandchildren

46:08.015 --> 46:10.309
that they can be anything".

46:17.733 --> 46:18.776
Yeah...

46:19.693 --> 46:21.111
-All right?
               -Yeah.

46:22.613 --> 46:23.781
I get that.

46:27.326 --> 46:32.372
It's so much bigger than us
          at this point,

46:32.414 --> 46:35.334
and I'm scared.

46:42.633 --> 46:43.842
I need you.

46:50.849 --> 46:51.892
Okay.

46:53.435 --> 46:54.478
I got you.

46:58.482 --> 46:59.566
I got you.

47:00.192 --> 47:01.276
You always got me.

47:02.069 --> 47:03.695
-Yes, I did.
         -It's a bad habit.

47:03.737 --> 47:06.114
-Thank God I got you.

47:07.324 --> 47:09.493
Lucky old me. Come on.

47:09.535 --> 47:13.330
I-I know--
 I know what this position means.

47:33.559 --> 47:34.601
Come in.

47:35.978 --> 47:38.689
Mrs. R,
     we were supposed to leave

47:38.730 --> 47:41.275
for your tour 20 minutes ago.

47:42.067 --> 47:43.944
The First Lady is waiting.

47:43.986 --> 47:47.990
I don't need a tour. Uncle Teddy
    lived there for eight years.

47:48.031 --> 47:49.867
I know,
       but it's part of the--

47:49.908 --> 47:51.535
Charade?

47:52.202 --> 47:53.620
Protocol.

47:53.662 --> 47:56.373
Why can't it wait till
      after the inauguration?

47:56.415 --> 47:59.042
There's plenty of time
           to reschedule.

47:59.084 --> 48:00.627
My appointment is a four-year--

48:00.669 --> 48:01.879
Sentence?

48:02.880 --> 48:03.964
Term.

48:05.173 --> 48:07.509
From your former students,
         wishing you luck.

48:07.551 --> 48:08.927
Oh.

48:08.969 --> 48:10.053
You haven't touched
          your breakfast.

48:10.095 --> 48:11.388
I had coffee.

48:11.430 --> 48:13.515
Mrs. R,
 you have an impossibly long day

48:13.557 --> 48:16.727
and your lunch isn't until 30,
     you have to eat something.

48:16.768 --> 48:19.771
Coffee is just fine.

48:19.813 --> 48:22.399
It's more than most Americans
        will have all day.

48:22.441 --> 48:24.318
All right, well, we don't have
      time to argue about it.

48:24.359 --> 48:25.944
Okay, let's get going.

48:25.986 --> 48:28.322
So, immediately following
            your tour,

48:28.363 --> 48:30.324
we're meeting with Edith Helm
      about the State dinner.

48:30.365 --> 48:32.993
Oh, is she staying on
       as social secretary?

48:33.035 --> 48:34.870
Mmm, better her than me.

48:34.912 --> 48:37.956
Then, we have decorators
       to meet with at noon.

48:37.998 --> 48:41.001
From shaping young minds
           to decorating.

48:41.043 --> 48:43.170
And I need to shift your meeting
             with Hick

48:43.211 --> 48:45.047
-for the APP's.
             -Oh, no.

48:45.088 --> 48:47.674
We'll give it an hour, probably
     sometime after 00 and--

48:47.716 --> 48:49.760
Oh, we'll need
      much more than an hour.

48:49.801 --> 48:51.762
It's just a few quotes
      about the inauguration.

48:51.803 --> 48:54.306
Oh, that's if you want it
        to be a pop piece.

48:59.853 --> 49:02.481
Senator.
 Senator, I understand all of it.

49:02.522 --> 49:04.900
All I am saying
    is that the democratic party

49:04.942 --> 49:08.403
has to be a united front
           from day one.

49:08.445 --> 49:10.322
Yes, thank you.

49:10.364 --> 49:13.283
Eleanor, aren't you supposed to
 be with the retiring First Lady?

49:13.325 --> 49:15.535
We're on our way.

49:15.577 --> 49:17.537
Will you make sure
        that he reads this?

49:17.579 --> 49:19.247
Uh, yes. Of course. What is it?

49:19.289 --> 49:21.124
It's my suggestions
     for cabinet appointments.

49:21.166 --> 49:23.126
-Okay. Both. 
    -Female ones.

49:23.168 --> 49:25.629
-Where are we with the speech?
 -Well, not as far as we would be

49:25.671 --> 49:27.255
were there not 40 other things
               to do.

49:27.297 --> 49:29.383
What's more important
      than the speech, Louis?

49:29.424 --> 49:32.177
-It's tomorrow.
     -I know. We'll get to it.

49:32.219 --> 49:35.097
Well, let me see a draft of it.
   I can cancel the First Lady.

49:35.138 --> 49:37.015
You can't cancel
          the First Lady.

49:37.057 --> 49:39.184
-I can cancel the First Lady.
     -I told her she couldn't.

49:39.226 --> 49:42.396
It's important that he lead
    with the cold, hard truth.

49:42.437 --> 49:44.022
Add some hope to it,

49:44.064 --> 49:46.483
but he needs to state the facts,
         plain and simple.

49:46.525 --> 49:48.944
There are 30 million Americans
            out of work

49:48.986 --> 49:50.237
and they don't want
        to be pandered to.

49:50.278 --> 49:51.405
Couldn't agree more.

49:51.446 --> 49:53.156
Left to his own devices,

49:53.198 --> 49:55.659
Franklin always errs on the side
     of optimism but we need to

49:55.701 --> 49:57.661
-strike the balance--
             -Mrs. R.

49:57.703 --> 50:00.122
Earl and the car have been
     outside for over an hour.

50:00.163 --> 50:02.624
-Oh, goodness.
   -That's entirely unnecessary.

50:02.666 --> 50:04.167
I'm going to walk.

50:04.209 --> 50:05.585
-You're not walking.
          -You can't walk.

50:05.627 --> 50:07.170
I most certainly am.

50:07.212 --> 50:09.006
-Mm-mmm.
 -Mrs. R, Lou Hoover is waiting,

50:09.047 --> 50:10.841
we really need to go.

50:10.882 --> 50:12.342
Yes, let's not keep her waiting.

50:12.384 --> 50:13.760
Louis, when can we talk
         about the speech?

50:13.802 --> 50:15.804
We will get to it
          this afternoon.

50:15.846 --> 50:17.597
Well, I'm all booked up
          this afternoon.

50:17.639 --> 50:19.016
Yes, I'm aware.

50:21.351 --> 50:23.020
Oh, I see.

50:23.061 --> 50:24.563
I'm good enough to get him here,

50:24.604 --> 50:26.356
but not good enough
          to keep going.

50:26.398 --> 50:28.900
You have your own schedule
          to worry about.

50:28.942 --> 50:30.861
-Your own duties.
            -Oh, good.

50:30.902 --> 50:35.407
So, he's finally decided on my
     job in the administration.

50:36.908 --> 50:38.869
Y-Yes, uh, First Lady.

50:43.457 --> 50:48.086
That's not a job, Louis.
      That's my circumstance.

50:51.298 --> 50:52.549
Shall we, Tommy?

50:53.759 --> 50:55.427
I need some fresh air.

51:20.744 --> 51:22.204
Is that terribly uncomfortable?

51:24.414 --> 51:26.833
I don't know.
   It's all pretty uncomfortable.

51:28.126 --> 51:30.378
-Can I help you in any way?
               -Hmm?

51:30.420 --> 51:32.464
Let me finish making breakfast
              for you.

51:33.090 --> 51:35.133
Okay...

51:36.259 --> 51:37.469
What is it?

51:46.144 --> 51:48.897
The Supreme court is ordering
           the president

51:48.939 --> 51:50.440
to release all the tapes.

51:52.818 --> 51:54.903
He'll have no choice
           but to resign.

52:00.283 --> 52:02.744
Well, that is news.

52:02.786 --> 52:04.287
Impeachment would only add
            to the pain

52:04.329 --> 52:05.789
the country is already in,

52:05.831 --> 52:07.958
resignation will be swift
           and definite.

52:09.835 --> 52:11.128
Betty...

52:12.921 --> 52:15.632
you must understand,
       the country needs me.

52:15.674 --> 52:18.135
-These last few months--
 -Oh, would you fucking spare me!

52:18.176 --> 52:19.386
Just for once.

52:21.304 --> 52:22.889
Thirteen campaigns...

52:26.184 --> 52:28.145
First the people
     of Grand Rapids need you,

52:28.186 --> 52:31.106
then the country needs you
    to take the vice presidency

52:31.148 --> 52:34.818
and now you're desperately
        needed as President.

52:34.860 --> 52:37.487
Can't you just be man enough
              to admit

52:37.529 --> 52:39.698
that you've always wanted this?

52:39.739 --> 52:42.159
I am a man of ambitions,
          Elizabeth. Yes.

52:42.200 --> 52:43.451
I want to succeed.

52:44.035 --> 52:45.620
I want to provide.

52:45.662 --> 52:47.455
But if you think I want

52:47.497 --> 52:49.124
what's being handed to me
     from this administration,

52:49.166 --> 52:52.043
and I realize my ambitions have
      made life hard for you.

52:53.545 --> 52:54.629
But you knew what you were
           getting into.

52:54.671 --> 52:56.006
-No!

52:56.047 --> 52:58.633
I did not know
      what I was getting into.

53:05.390 --> 53:07.726
But here I am.

53:15.025 --> 53:16.735
And I will be here for you.

53:19.905 --> 53:21.698
But I am going to be myself.

53:21.740 --> 53:24.367
I am going to do and say things
        that I believe in.

53:24.409 --> 53:26.369
I think I've earned that right.

53:28.079 --> 53:30.999
I'm going to take a shower.
      You can finish up here.

53:31.041 --> 53:32.375
Betty...

53:39.591 --> 53:40.675
Thank you.

53:42.260 --> 53:43.887
Are Pat and Julie okay?

53:43.929 --> 53:44.971
I don't--

53:45.764 --> 53:46.890
I--

53:48.058 --> 53:49.684
I'm sure it's difficult.

53:54.022 --> 53:55.065
Yes, it is.
